      <hedline>
        <hl1>Make Cabs Accessible</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Michael Volkman letter says accessible taxi service is badly needed by wheelchair-bound people like himself (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Rule Proposed to Make New Cabs Accessible to Wheelchair Users'' (news article, June 29):</p>
        <p>As a wheelchair user, I find that taking the train to New York City from my home in Albany is a cinch; it is only when the elevator brings me up from the depths of Penn Station and deposits me onto the street that the adventure begins. What would otherwise be a routine car trip takes far longer on city buses.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Rule Proposed to Make New Cabs Accessible to Wheelchair Users'' (news article, June 29):</p>
        <p>As a wheelchair user, I find that taking the train to New York City from my home in Albany is a cinch; it is only when the elevator brings me up from the depths of Penn Station and deposits me onto the street that the adventure begins. What would otherwise be a routine car trip takes far longer on city buses.</p>
        <p>Accessible taxi service is badly needed. New York is a center of business, commerce, culture and tourism.  All of New York's services must be accessible to everyone who wants to use them.</p>
        <p>MICHAEL VOLKMAN  Albany, June 29, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
